We are partners of many organisations whome we host joint programs with. &#xd;
&#xd;
As mentioned we are a well respected organisation in the UN system, we are also a listed member on the 'Commission on the Status of Women.' We also hold ECOSOC status within the UN system (ECOSOC means, United Nations Economic and Social Council Status), which is only given to trusted and respected organisations and NGO's within the UN system. &#xd;
&#xd;
http://www.un.org/en/ecosoc/&#xd;
&#xd;
We are also members of CSW, which is the Commission on the Status of Women. &#xd;
&#xd;
http://www.unwomen.org/en/csw&#xd;
&#xd;
We are also partners and participators in the Beijing Platform for Action &#xd;
&#xd;
http://beijing20.unwomen.org/en&#xd;
&#xd;
Our network of partners include the NGO committee on Women in Switzerland&#xd;
http://www.ngocsw-geneva.ch/&#xd;
&#xd;
UNESCO&#xd;
http://en.unesco.org/&#xd;
&#xd;
Global Alliance on Media and Gender&#xd;
http://www.unesco.org/new/en/communication-and-information/crosscutting-priorities/gender-and-media/global-alliance-on-media-and-gender/about-gamag/&#xd;
&#xd;
Food and Agricultural Organisation FAO&#xd;
http://www.fao.org/employment/en/&#xd;
&#xd;
You will see that we have a history of work with the above organisations, where we have partnered with them on seminars, projects and publications. &#xd;
&#xd;
You will find this information on our website and I have also provided the links above.

